-- slice 4: pass a NAMED top-level function as a VALUE to a higher-order function.
-- `double` is a known top-level fn; used unapplied it must become a closure too —
-- an eta/static closure (captureless) whose lifted body forwards to @mdk_double —
-- so the indirect call inside `applyTo` works uniformly.
double x = x * 2
applyTo f x = f x
main = applyTo double 21
